[~tony], [~tjcramer]: how one would go to allow a user to describe the instance types? I tried the action describeinstancetype (with 's' and without), describeVMtype etc ... to not avail. If I add a policy like

{code}
{
   "Statement":[{
      "Sid": "policy1",
      "Effect":"Allow",
      "Action":["ec2:describe*"],
      "Resource":"*",
      }
   ]
}
{code}

it works. 

Which one is the proper action?

Confirmed that in 4.0 you can add a policy as follows:

{code}
{
  "Statement": [
   {
      "Action": [
        "ec2:DescribeInstanceTypes"
      ],
      "Effect": "Deny",
      "Resource": [
       "arn:aws:ec2:::vmtype/m1.small",
       "arn:aws:ec2:::vmtype/m1.large"
      ]
    } ]
}
{code}

To deny access to specific vm types for an account or a user (if the user has another policy granting access)
